@Tratcher Took me a while, but I managed to integrate redis and WebSockets messaging over a cluster of servers.
Which makes me think, since it worked so nicely, why isn't it in the RC? Do I need to fear from performance issues? crashes? we plan to go live-production with our application when RC2 will be released... :fearful: Do you think it's a bad idea adding WebSockets to it (it's not a mandatory feature)?

Thanks a lot for the hint and help!

@Tratcher Unless I'm missing something obvious, the timer only sends pings which is quite useless unless we can plugin to the pipeline and take actions if no pong was received. 

